ğŸ“œ 2. What Is Contract Testing (and Why Pact?)

This gives context before diving into the mechanics.

Example:

Contract testing ensures that two services â€” a consumer and a provider â€” can communicate correctly without requiring full end-to-end integration.

Using the Pact framework, the consumer defines a contract that specifies what it expects from the provider (request â†’ response pairs).
The provider then verifies this contract against its actual implementation, ensuring compatibility before deployment.

Pact eliminates the need for heavy integration environments by treating contracts as executable agreements between services.

